omo Mantegazza (Italian, 1853-1920)\n* [[Georges Henri Manzana Pissarro]] (French, 1871-1961) \n* [[Vincente March|Vicente March y Marco]] (Spanish, 1859-1927)<ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\u00e9cole Espagnole,'' ACR edition, 1997, p. 162</ref>  [[:es:Vicente March]]\n* Ludovico Marchetti (Italian, 1853-1909)\n* [[David Samuel Margoliouth|D.S. Margoliouth]] (English, 1858-1940) \n* [[Pompeo Mariani]] (Italian, 1857-1927)\n* [[Prosper Marilhat]] (French, 1811-1847)<ref>Davies, K., ''Orientalists: Western Artists in Arabia, the Sahara, Persia and India,'' New York, Laynfaroh, 2005, p. 24</ref>\n* [[Vincenzo Marinelli]] (Italian, 1820-1892)\n* Isidoro Mar\u00edn Gar\u00e9s (Spanish, 1863-1926)<ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\u00e9cole Espagnole,'' ACR edition, 1997, p. 165</ref>\n* Enrique Mar\u00edn Sevilla (Spanish, 1876-1940)  <ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\u00e9cole Espagnole,'' ACR edition, 1997, pp 163-64</ref>\n* [[Ram\u00f3n Mart\u00ed Alsina|Ram\u00f3n Mart\u00ed i Alsina]] (Spanish, 1826-1894) \n* Juan Gim\u00e9nez Mart\u00edn (Spanish, 1855-1901) [[:es:Juan Gim\u00e9nez Mart\u00edn]] \n* Juan Pozo Mart\u00ednez (Spanish, ?-?)<ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\u00e9cole Espagnole,'' ACR edition, 1997, p. 170 (translated from French) </ref>\n* [[Maria Martinetti]] (Italian, 1864-1921)\n* Yvonne Mariotte (French, 1909-?)\n* Fran\u00e7ois de Marliave (French, 1847-1953) [[:fr:Fran\u00e7ois de Marliave]]\n* Tom\u00e1s Mart\u00edn Rebollo (Spanish, 1858-1919) <ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\u00e9cole Espagnole,'' ACR edition, 1997, p. 168</ref>\n* [[Arcadi Mas i Fondevila|Arcadio Mas i Fondevila]] (Spanish, 1852-1934)\n* [[Frank Henry Mason]] (British, 1876-1965)\n* [[Francesc Masriera|Francisco Masriera y Manovens]] catalan: Francesc Masriera i Manovens (Spanish, 1842-1902)\n* [[Henri Matisse]] (French, 1869-1954) \n* Virgilio Mattoni de la Fuente (Spanish, 1842-1923) <ref>Caso, E.D., ''Les Orientalistes de l'\